04054nam a22005295i 9781554589548DE-B159720240306010644.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||240306t20142014xxc    fo  d z      eng d  a97815545895487 a10.51644/97815545895482doi  a(DE-B1597)667861  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  axxccCA 7aSOC0310002bisacsh04a305.8009711 aFleras, Augie, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aRacisms in a Multicultural Canada :bParadoxes, Politics, and Resistance /cAugie Fleras. 1aWaterloo, Ontario : bWilfrid Laurier University Press, c[2014] 4c©2014  a1 online resource (330 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFront Matter -- tContents -- tPreface -- tReappraising Racism -- tThe Politics of Racism -- tReconceptualizing Racism -- tThe Riddles Of Race -- tDeconstructing Racism -- tHow Racisms Work -- tInterpersonal Racisms -- tInstitutional Racisms -- tIdeological Racisms -- tInfrastructural Racisms -- tIvory Tower Racisms -- tExplaining Racisms, Erasing Racisms -- tContesting Racisms -- tRooting Out Racisms -- tOfficial Multiculturalism -- tSummary and Conclusion -- tReferences -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aIn acknowledging the possibility that as the world changes so too does racism, this book argues that racism is not disappearing, despite claims of living in a post-racial and multicultural world. To the contrary, racisms persist by transforming into different forms whose intent or effects remain the same: to deny and disallow as well as to exclude and exploit. Racisms in a Multicultural Canada is organized around the assumption that race is not simply a set of categories and that racism is not just a collection of individuals with bad attitudes. Rather, racism is as much a matter of interests as of attitudes, of property as of prejudice, of structural advantage as of personal failing, of whiteness as of the “other,” of discourse as of discrimination, and of unequal power relations as of bigotry. This multi-dimensionality of racism complicates the challenge of formulating anti-racism and anti-colonialist strategies capable of addressing it. Employing a critical framework that puts politics and power at the centre of analysis, this book focuses on why racisms proliferate, how they work in contemporary societies, and how the way we think and talk about racism changes over time. Specifically, it examines the working of contemporary racisms in a multicultural Canada that claims to abide by principles of multiculturalism and a commitment to a post-racial society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aRacismxCanada. 0aRacismzCanada. 0aRacismexCanada. 4aSocial Science: Multiculturalism. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Discrimination & Race Relations.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311127407208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2014z978311127709740uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978155458954840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781554589548423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781554589548/original  a978-3-11-127407-2  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014b2014  a978-3-11-127709-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles